Roma part 1. 🇮🇹🫶🏼🍕

Roma part 2. 🇮🇹🫶🏼🍝🍷
⠀⠀⠀⠀
Recommendations:
- Cooking class. We did ours at Via Giuseppe Zanardelli 14 Eat and Walk Italy - at Gusto Restaurant. It was great! 
- Rome food tour
- The best time to see the Trevi Fountain is early morning (before 9 am)
- Map out your day beforehand with the address to each spot saved in a note on your phone so you’re not waisting your time trying to plan it on the spot.
- We walked / took a taxi everywhere and it worked great. But definitely wear comfortable shoes because it’s a lot of walking. I didn’t want to deal with pick pocketers on the train/subway.
⠀⠀⠀⠀
What recommendations or tips did I miss? Comment them below so others can save them 🤗🤍

Roma part 3. 🇮🇹🏛️🍝🍷🤍

Tips if you’re starting your Europe trip in Rome:
- If at all possible use your points and get the business class seat with the sleeping pods (something I didn’t do and I fully regret). There is nothing worse than starting out a long trip exhausted.
- If business class seats are not an option don’t stress, just plan on your first day in Rome being a rest day! I would not recommend making any reservations or scheduling any tours. The first day is very hard because most flights from the US to Rome are overnight flights so you land in Rome in the morning extremely exhausted from not getting any sleep. And you usually can’t check into your hotel until 3 or 4 so you’re very limited when it comes to showering, changing and resting after a long flight. I would suggest the first day be a recovery / chill day where you go to a cafe, maybe walk around and just explore with no plans or agenda, go to a yummy restaurant (The food is amazing everywhere and there are so many places you can just walk up and eat without needing a reservation. That way you can just go eat when you want to rather than being tied down to a specific time) and then go back to the hotel/airbnb and go to bed early!
- I personally think you need a minimum of 3 nights in Rome to see everything!
Day 1: Land in Rome. Rest and recovery day! 
Day 2: Explore, tour, reservations, etc. 
Day 3: Explore, tour, reservations, etc. 
Day 4: Leave early in the morning to go to your next destination!
- Everyone told us to pack in a carry on but I couldn’t get 15 days in a carry on 😂🙈. Turns out having a big suitcase was no issue at all for us. We took a private transfer from the airport to the hotel. And then a private transfer back to the airport to our next destination. There was never a time our whole trip that we had to “drag our suitcase across cobblestone streets”.
- We flew to all of our destinations rather than taking the train. It was quick, easy, safe, and cheap! (Flights within Europe are super cheap) Price breakdown and more tips in the comments. 

Have you ever been to Rome? What are your tips? Curious your thoughts! I love hearing everyone’s different opinions! 🤗

The Vatican a series 🤍🏛️✨🇻🇦🌱🖼️
⠀⠀⠀⠀
I’ve never been a big history girl but something about the Vatican stole my heart. I don’t know if it was the stories, the history, the architecture, the art, the details, or a little bit of it all! But from one non history girl to another, this is a tour worth going to!
⠀⠀⠀⠀
Tip: do the semi-private or private tour. You’ll be able to see everything a lot better and enjoy it more without being so cramped by the crowds!

Last night with a 4 year old and I am not well 😭🥹 How is my baby going to be 5 tomorrow??? Like what??!!!🥺 idk what it is but something about 5 just seems so much older like he is a legit kid. No longer a baby or toddler 😭 I can’t handle it!! Time please slow down 🤍

Happy birthday to my baby!!! (A week late because Disney was too fun to stop and post on insta) You truly are the light of my world! There’s no one who can light up a room like you and your joy is so contagious. You have the worlds biggest, most tender heart and love like no other. Everyone that comes in contact with you is blown away because you’re wise beyond your years. The way you hear from the Lord so clearly at such a young age blows me away daily. And the spiritual gifts the Lord has given you are already touching so many lives and everyday I wake up in awe that I get to witness it and call you mine! You’re too cute for your own good and your charm and sense of humor is gonna get me in trouble when you’re older 😂🙈 But right now it’s still so innocent and makes me laugh everyday. I’m so beyond proud of everything you have had to overcome at such a young age. You’ve handled every hurdle thrown at you with so much strength and grace and you’re gonna make a damn good husband and father one day because of it. You’re my twin in male form and I wish I had the words to express how thankful and healing that is for me. You LOVE to learn. You’re a sponge that can’t get enough. Your favorite things right now are: animals, legos, Minecraft, rollercoasters, baseball, soccer, traveling, the beach, swimming, snuggles, and smoked salmon haha. You’re truly my favorite person to hangout with and I’m so excited to see what year 5 brings! I love you with my whole heart 🤍🫶🏼 Happy 5th birthday Bestie!

Thanksgiving is a really hard day for me. It’s become a holiday that is filled with so much grief. It’s a day that consists of me sitting in a room silently suffering while everyone around me is filled with so much joy and thanksgiving. Yesterday marked my 3rd thanksgiving without my little boy. And for the first time since my divorce I didn’t force myself to put a smile on and act like it was okay. I celebrated with him the day before and then I did absolutely nothing on actual thanksgiving day. Normally I would go and put a smile on my face and tell myself that I still have so much to be grateful for, that it’s just another day, it’s not that big of a deal unless I make it a big deal, and that there are so many people who have it worse than me today, etc etc. And while yes all those things are true, what else is true is how utterly unfair and beyond heartbreaking it is that I suffer yet again for a 3rd year in a row without my son, without my dad, and without so many other things that aren’t public knowledge, all because of things that were out of my control. 

I decided this thanksgiving I wasn’t going to force myself to override how I felt nor show up to the family events and force myself to put a smile on my face and be positive for everyone else’s comfort. Instead my heart needed to accept reality and feel the reality of the pain that this day actually causes me. I did absolutely nothing yesterday. I sat on the couch alone and I let myself be angry, be heartbroken, and feel the million other feelings that flooded my heart and my mind. I let myself admit that I’m not thankful for the reality that I now come from a broken family and have a broken family myself. 

I grieved the fact I couldn’t even get on Instagram and interact with my friends and family because I had to guard my own heart. I knew I would get mad and angry looking at everyone else and their posts of their not broken families, smiling and saying how thankful they were while I was crying over mine. And that’s not fair or kind to them. Nor is it good or healthy for me to get mad at other people’s blessings I so desperately sometimes wish I had… (cont. in the comments)
